    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-05T04:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-05T04:34:00-05:00" n="650"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1452: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-05T18:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 5—3:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Czech authorities desire to decorate some members of Service Corps in recognition
                    of their efficient work evacuation. Is it permissible under the rules of
                    service? If possible should be allowed as without their work evacuation would be
                    much more difficult to accomplish.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
